@startuml class_diagram_calculator

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle bold

class Calculator {
    + add(a, b) : numeric
    + subtract(a, b) : numeric
    + multiply(a, b) : numeric
    + divide(a, b) : float
}

class TestDivision {
    + test_divide_positive_numbers(calc)
    + test_divide_with_floats(calc)
    + test_divide_negative_numbers(calc)
    + test_divide_by_zero_raises_exception(calc)
    + test_divide_zero_by_nonzero(calc)
    + test_divide_non_numeric_inputs_raise_typeerror(calc, invalid_a, invalid_b) <<parametrized: 6 cases>>
    + test_divide_result_precision(calc)
    + test_divide_large_numbers(calc)
    + test_divide_very_small_numbers(calc)
}

class "calc()" <<fixture>> {
    Creates a Calculator instance per test.
    Injected into every TestDivision test method.
}

TestDivision ..> Calculator : depends on
TestDivision ..> "calc()" : uses

note right of TestDivision
  pytest test class
  All methods receive a Calculator
  instance via the calc() fixture.
end note

@enduml
